cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is about enhancing language representation models with knowledge graphs, which is a common topic in natural language processing (NLP) research. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves machine learning techniques and models, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses improving performance on knowledge-driven tasks, which could place it in cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
